Update LDAP and database configurations for improved security.
Replaced hardcoded LDAP settings in `application.properties` with updated credentials and Base64-encoded password decoding for better security. Removed Oracle-specific configurations, streamlining dependency management and aligning setup with environment-based properties.

Add Oracle and PostgreSQL support with JPA configurations
Introduced entity classes and Hibernate configuration for Oracle and PostgreSQL databases. Updated dependencies and application properties to enable JPA integration and database-specific settings. This facilitates multi-database support and improves project flexibility.

Refactor database operations and services integration
Integrated service layer for improved separation of concerns and code maintainability. Replaced direct database operations in controllers with service calls, implemented new repository interfaces, and refactored redundant or outdated methods. Simplifies logic and prepares codebase for further scalability.

Refactor services and remove deprecated functionality
Removed unused QsAdminUsersService class and simplified file handling in CSVReaderService. Migrated DB operations to service-based architecture, ensuring better separation of concerns. Replaced redundant database initialization and Qlik connector setup logic in controllers with streamlined service calls. Updated configurations for better property management.
TODO: Fix most of items and code.

Refactor JSPs and controllers to streamline paths and logic
Updated JSP files to use `pageContext.request.contextPath` for dynamic paths and replaced scriptlets with JSTL tags as part of modernization efforts. Refactored controllers by introducing helper methods for reusability and concise role/user handling, while improving code readability and maintainability.

Remove unused files and improve CSVReaderService logging
Deleted obsolete Java models, JSP files, and configuration classes to clean up the project. Enhanced `CSVReaderService` by adding error logs for failed file creation, improving debugging and maintainability.

Update PostgreSQL driver to version 42.3.3
Upgraded the PostgreSQL JDBC dependency from 42.2.27 to 42.3.3 in the pom.xml file. This ensures compatibility with recent database updates and includes important bug fixes and performance improvements.

Refactor roles list initialization and update dependencies
Replaced static roles list initialization with a dynamic method in `RolesListConfig` for improved flexibility. Added CORS configuration in `Config`, updated Maven dependencies for Oracle and Spring Boot, and enhanced repository settings for better compatibility.

Remove Oracle and PostgreSQL configurations and refactor models.
Removed Oracle and PostgreSQL database configurations, along with related properties and Java classes, to streamline dependency management. Refactored model classes and JSP files, standardizing identifiers and improving naming conventions for better readability. Updated `ManagementController` to use consistent types, replaced static date handling with `OffsetDateTime`, and adjusted dependencies in the application setup.

Remove Oracle configurations and update dependency handling.
Oracle-related configurations, properties, and classes were removed to streamline the application. Updated `OracleDbConfig` to decode Base64 passwords directly via the `Environment`, improving security and flexibility. Adjusted dependency management to reflect the changes in the data source setup.

Remove Oracle-specific configurations and refactor database setup.
Eliminated `OracleDataSourceProperties` and adjusted `OracleDbConfig` to use environment properties with Base64-decoded passwords. Updated `application.properties` to reflect changes in credentials. This simplifies the configuration and enhances security by removing hardcoded dependencies.

Update LDAP and database configurations for improved security.
Replaced hardcoded LDAP settings in `application.properties` with updated credentials and Base64-encoded password decoding for better security. Removed Oracle-specific configurations, streamlining dependency management and aligning setup with environment-based properties.
